	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Coreopsis calliopsidea, Mentzelia pectinata, Monolopia </i>spp., and/or <i>Camissonia boothii </i>seasonally dominant or co-dominant with a variety of other native herbs (Buck-Diaz and Evens 2011, Buck-Diaz et al. 2013).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Flats, mud hills, and clay beds or moderate to steep, dry, often south-facing slopes. Fine-textured soils derived from ancient lakebed deposits and siltstone, gypsum, or other sedimentary rocks.  </div>
</div>

        
